# Whitelist for `clasp push` (gitignore semantics, clasp 3.x).
#
# Root-anchored patterns only ignore top-level entries, so we can re-include
# the `src/` directory without violating gitignore's "parent dir cannot
# be re-included" rule. Everything inside `src/` is pushed by default.
# The prior pattern (`**` + `!src/**`) silently excluded everything
# under clasp 3.x and made CI fail with "Pushed 0 files".

/*
/.*

!/appsscript.json
!/src
